Durban - Female members of the South African National Defence Force (SANDF), the SA Police Services (SANDF), the Road Traffic Inspectorate (RTI), the SA Navy and the Durban Metro Police marched through Dr Pixley KaSeme (West) Street on Friday as part of the 2018 Women Imbokodo Armed Forces Parade in Durban. The event forms part of the Women’s Month commemorations and snaked through the city centre with more than 500 participants. The march was expected to end at city hall where they were going to be addressed by eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede. The parade started at 9am with traffic around the area re-routed by Durban Metro Police. Traffic around the city centre was backed up in several areas as motorists, unaware of the parade found themselves stuck in traffic. The Durban Metro Police said that it had advised motorists of the road closures earlier in the week and suggested alternate routes. Daily News  